</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFEB55E4AFDE02553" authority="Simon, 1901" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[298,599,1026,1050]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFEB55E4AFE7B2553" box="[298,460,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Hurius vulpinus</emphasis>
Simon, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB639605748FFACFF085E00FC3C245F" blockId="15.[151,1437,1096,1483]" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFF085E00FEC4252B" bold="true" box="[151,371,1096,1122]" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFE755E01FD8F252B" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[490,568,1097,1122]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFE755E01FD8F252B" box="[490,568,1097,1122]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Hurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFCB35E00FC21252B" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[812,918,1096,1122]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFCB35E00FC21252B" box="[812,918,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Scoturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFC4F5E01FB83252B" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2015" box="[976,1076,1097,1122]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Urupuyu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFC4F5E01FB83252B" box="[976,1076,1097,1122]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Urupuyu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a single-lobed RTA; in addition, males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFE135E25FE6D25CF" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[396,474,1133,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFE135E25FE6D25CF" box="[396,474,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Hurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFD535E24FCEF25CF" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[716,856,1132,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Admesturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFD535E24FCEF25CF" box="[716,856,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Admesturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFCF75E24FC7825CF" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[872,975,1132,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFCF75E24FC7825CF" box="[872,975,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Atelurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFC415E24FBE925CF" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[990,1118,1132,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFC415E24FBE925CF" box="[990,1118,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFB005E24FABA25CF" authorityName="Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" box="[1183,1293,1132,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Guriurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFB005E24FABA25CF" box="[1183,1293,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Guriurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a RvTA densely covered by strong and long spicules. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFCEB5ED9FC7525E3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[884,962,1169,1194]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFCEB5ED9FC7525E3" box="[884,962,1169,1194]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Hurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFB2A5ED8FAA825E3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[1205,1311,1168,1194]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFB2A5ED8FAA825E3" box="[1205,1311,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Scoturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFAB05ED8FA2125E3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[1327,1430,1168,1194]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFAB05ED8FA2125E3" box="[1327,1430,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Atelurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFF085EFDFF4C2587" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2015" box="[151,251,1205,1230]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Urupuyu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFF085EFDFF4C2587" box="[151,251,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Urupuyu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFEA45EFCFE0C2587" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[315,443,1204,1230]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFEA45EFCFE0C2587" box="[315,443,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by not having the copulatory openings forming an atrium, and from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFAB15EFCFA2B2587" authorityName="Marta, Bustamante, Ruiz &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" box="[1326,1436,1204,1230]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Guriurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFAB15EFCFA2B2587" box="[1326,1436,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Guriurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by not having the ducts covered by a sclerotized plate; also, females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFC295E91FBB325BB" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[950,1028,1241,1266]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFC295E91FBB325BB" box="[950,1028,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Hurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFB725E90FACE25BB" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[1261,1401,1240,1266]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Admesturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFB725E90FACE25BB" box="[1261,1401,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Admesturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having separate coupling pockets on the sides of the epigynal plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
